1
00:00:03,545 --> 00:00:06,798
(Yukiya) There's no way in my life I'll ever be able to forgive you.

2
00:00:06,881 --> 00:00:08,967
(Nobuo) What happened? Today we are two people again

3
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:09,968
(Male) Yukiya Ise

4
00:00:10,051 --> 00:00:13,638
9:19 p.m. Arrested on suspicion of violating the Specified Secrets Protection Act

5
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:14,973
(Reo) It's my own fault.

6
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:30,405
(Sound of door opening and closing)

7
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:38,288
 (sekibarai)

8
00:00:39,497 --> 00:00:42,584
(Nobuo) Yukiya-kun, it’s been a while.

9
00:00:43,126 --> 00:00:45,045
(Nobuo) Do you remember uncle?

10
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:48,298
The last time we met...

11
00:00:48,381 --> 00:00:51,843
Are you sure that was Masa-kun's wedding?

12
00:00:51,926 --> 00:00:53,136
7 years ago

13
00:00:58,016 --> 00:00:58,933
Where is this?

14
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:02,353
Yeah? Aoyama Police Station

15
00:01:05,482 --> 00:01:06,691
(laughter)

16
00:01:07,692 --> 00:01:10,445
Don't make that face

17
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:14,032
Don't worry, I'm here.

18
00:01:14,115 --> 00:01:16,576
If there's nothing, I can give it to you right away.

19
00:01:17,619 --> 00:01:19,329
There is no way

20
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:22,248
What is it?

21
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:29,214
(Nobuo) Indeed...

22
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:33,176
Yukiya-kun from a long time ago⸺

23
00:01:33,259 --> 00:01:35,261
I was good at computers.

24
00:01:39,974 --> 00:01:41,684
Sei-chan also said so.

25
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:44,145
They say you have talent in that area.

26
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:49,526
…I’m sure⸺

27
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:52,570
Last year I was with Sei-chan...

28
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:57,909
Even though I quit because I was angry⸺

29
00:01:58,701 --> 00:02:02,247
State secrets was too much.

30
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,542
State secret?

31
00:02:10,505 --> 00:02:12,048
It makes some sense...

32
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:14,926
Even my uncle is sad

33
00:02:15,593 --> 00:02:19,973
The youngest son of the Ise family is a dangerous person who threatens the nation.

34
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:23,476
Please be careful

35
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:28,147
In short, you should never touch someone⸺

36
00:02:28,231 --> 00:02:30,441
That I made you angry

37
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:39,951
You know what? He's a good adult

38
00:02:51,921 --> 00:02:53,631
(Masayuki) As expected, Nobuo-san

39
00:02:55,049 --> 00:02:57,093
(Masayuki) The next Prime Minister

40
00:02:57,176 --> 00:02:59,053
(Erika) It's true.

41
00:03:01,472 --> 00:03:03,641
(Masayuki) This guy is an idiot.

42
00:03:03,725 --> 00:03:04,767
Fufufufu…

43
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:07,395
you were good

44
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:10,732
A member of the Ise family

45
00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:24,495
(Officer) Come in.

46
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:37,550
(Sound of door closing) (Sound of locking)

47
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:48,895
‪♪～

48
00:04:44,909 --> 00:04:46,911
‪～♪

49
00:05:10,518 --> 00:05:11,602
(Officer) Breakfast.

50
00:05:17,608 --> 00:05:18,609
take it

51
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:22,822
eat quickly

52
00:05:24,407 --> 00:05:25,867
Are you feeling unwell?

53
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:34,959
(Masayuki) Oh, you drink a lot.

54
00:05:35,043 --> 00:05:38,755
This is my first time trying German-made powdered milk, but I think I like it.

55
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:39,714
Hey?

56
00:05:42,884 --> 00:05:44,343
What about your father today?

57
00:05:45,511 --> 00:05:48,473
(Fuyu) I haven't seen you since this morning.

58
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:10,995
(mobile phone vibrator)

59
00:06:25,051 --> 00:06:26,594
knock)

60
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:28,971
(Seiichiro) Yes.

61
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:30,139
(sound of door opening)

62
00:06:31,307 --> 00:06:33,643
- (Masayuki) Excuse me - (Erika) Excuse me

63
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:35,728
(sound of door closing)

64
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:47,532
what happened?

65
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:53,204
I received a call from the Ise Medical Center this morning.

66
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:58,709
It seems that Kaho has woken up.

67
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:06,008
Found while trying to escape from the facility

68
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:11,180
It seems like it was tough, he went wild.

69
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:12,557
-(Nurse) Hanaho-san-(Nurse) It's okay.

70
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:14,100
(Nurse) Please calm down.

71
00:07:14,183 --> 00:07:15,560
(Nurse) It's okay to take it slow.

72
00:07:15,643 --> 00:07:17,645
-(Nurse) It's okay.-(Nurse) It's okay.

73
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:21,065
- (Nurse) It's okay, Hanaho-san - (Nurse) It's okay, it's okay.

74
00:07:26,487 --> 00:07:28,698
He says he almost got killed.

75
00:07:36,414 --> 00:07:37,665
To you guys

76
00:07:38,624 --> 00:07:44,130
footsteps)

77
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:56,976
Answer!

78
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:16,871
haven't done anything

79
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:25,338
Masayuki-san found Hanaho-san collapsed...

80
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:31,636
I can't think of anything but suicide.

81
00:08:34,805 --> 00:08:38,476
It's impossible for us to try to kill you, right?

82
00:08:42,772 --> 00:08:44,357
Is that so?

83
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:46,484
yes

84
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:56,202
What do you think?

85
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:04,335
Hanaho is now...

86
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:07,296
I'm sleeping

87
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:13,302
What I'm asking is the truth or falsity of Hanaho's statement.

88
00:09:17,682 --> 00:09:18,849
Masayuki

89
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:24,647
We are...

90
00:09:34,657 --> 00:09:36,492
haven't done anything

91
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:42,873
Got it

92
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:51,882
No matter what she says in the future, don't be upset.

93
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:54,802
Okay?

94
00:09:56,304 --> 00:10:01,392
Don't change your words no matter what

95
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:06,314
yes

96
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:10,735
yes

97
00:10:34,425 --> 00:10:37,136
(Seiichiro) Too bad, it's over now.

98
00:10:37,219 --> 00:10:41,223
-(Fuyu) No, I'll take it down.-(Seiichiro) Yeah, thank you.

99
00:10:43,559 --> 00:10:44,477
Hey

100
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:47,438
Do you understand?

101
00:11:09,251 --> 00:11:11,045
(sound of door closing)

102
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:45,121
Huh! Ha ha...

103
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:48,457
Ha ha...

104
00:12:04,181 --> 00:12:08,811
(Yukiya in childhood) ♪ Twinkle Hikaru

105
00:12:08,894 --> 00:12:13,190
(Yukiya) ♪ The star of the sky

106
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:17,778
(Saori/Yukiya) ♪ If you blink,

107
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:22,199
♪ I'm watching everyone

108
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:26,454
♪ Twinkle Hikaru

109
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:31,125
♪ The star of the sky

110
00:12:34,962 --> 00:12:36,589
-(Saori) Yukiya-(Yukiya) Yeah?

111
00:12:38,132 --> 00:12:42,470
Even if this factory becomes part of the Ise Group⸺

112
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:49,185
The time and memories spent here will remain in my heart forever.

113
00:12:50,895 --> 00:12:54,231
So... it's okay

114
00:13:36,732 --> 00:13:38,275
Hanaho-sama

115
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:51,121
(Yukiya) You might not betray me.

116
00:13:51,622 --> 00:13:53,791
Maybe I won't bully you

117
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:56,168
but…

118
00:13:56,252 --> 00:13:58,337
not on your side

119
00:13:59,338 --> 00:14:03,300
After all, he is a servant of the Ise family.

120
00:14:12,017 --> 00:14:15,437
(birds chirping)

121
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:37,418
footsteps)

122
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:39,378
(Officer) It's food. Open it.

123
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:42,881
It's decided, open it.

124
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:56,061
How long are you planning on not eating?

125
00:14:57,354 --> 00:14:58,898
Eat carefully!

126
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:03,986
(footsteps leaving)

127
00:15:22,713 --> 00:15:25,799
I have transferred the money, please check it.

128
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:33,140
(Reo) Thank you

129
00:15:33,807 --> 00:15:37,686
But I was saved, thanks for your cooperation.

130
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:40,314
Of course

131
00:15:41,065 --> 00:15:44,109
I have been indebted to Erika before.

132
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:45,778
And⸺

133
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:51,241
Yukiya Ise only feels betrayed.

134
00:15:52,826 --> 00:15:56,497
Thank you for telling me the truth

135
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:02,586
you're tough being you

136
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:06,340
Bring the members along to make your dreams come true

137
00:16:09,343 --> 00:16:12,262
You can't live without money

138
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:14,390
(Reo) Yes.

139
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:17,184
It's me⸺

140
00:16:17,893 --> 00:16:21,480
I don't trust people who don't care about money.

141
00:16:22,106 --> 00:16:25,192
You can live in a daze, right?

142
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:27,569
I get irritated when I see things like that

143
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:29,780
Huh...

144
00:16:31,031 --> 00:16:35,411
That's why I'm trying to rebuild the team somehow.

145
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:38,414
I'm rooting for Satake-san.

146
00:16:40,457 --> 00:16:43,460
I think I suffered badly in that incident.

147
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:46,714
But don't blame yourself

148
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:50,926
It's his fault for taking advantage of people's dreams.

149
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:54,013
yes

150
00:16:57,766 --> 00:17:00,269
I wish I could be punished for this incident.

151
00:17:00,936 --> 00:17:04,898
Can you help me again if something happens?

152
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:07,067
Yeah

153
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:13,240
Thank you, of course I will add the reward.

154
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:18,412
I...

155
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:26,003
I trust Erika.

156
00:17:27,171 --> 00:17:28,005
Huh?

157
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:31,091
(Reo) For giving me a job⸺

158
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:34,094
He promises a commensurate reward

159
00:17:37,306 --> 00:17:38,849
thank you

160
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:49,401
footsteps)

161
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:53,781
(Officer) Number 31, I'm meeting you.

162
00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:14,426
(sound of lock opening)

163
00:18:27,022 --> 00:18:28,357
knock)

164
00:18:40,661 --> 00:18:41,954
(Officer) Sit down.

165
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:53,799
It's kind of cold here

166
00:18:58,178 --> 00:18:59,847
What do you mean?

167
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:02,891
(Erika) I had no intention of doing anything...

168
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:05,686
Yukiya was the one who betrayed me first, right?

169
00:19:06,436 --> 00:19:07,312
(Yukiya) Huh?

170
00:19:08,105 --> 00:19:10,274
As long as you behave like a member of the Ise family⸺

171
00:19:10,357 --> 00:19:12,818
I didn't have to do this either.

172
00:19:19,867 --> 00:19:21,535
feel ill

173
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:25,289
Why are you so obsessed with us?

174
00:19:30,169 --> 00:19:32,838
Forget about this⸺

175
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:35,799
I wish I could just live my life

176
00:19:36,758 --> 00:19:39,428
Because it doesn't matter anymore

177
00:19:45,392 --> 00:19:46,310
what?

178
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:49,980
but…

179
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:54,526
We were once a couple

180
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,529
(Erika) Hehehehe...

181
00:19:58,864 --> 00:19:59,740
Huh...

182
00:20:01,491 --> 00:20:02,784
I agree

183
00:20:05,913 --> 00:20:08,332
For letting me into the Ise family⸺

184
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:11,418
I'm grateful

185
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:06,098
Sorry

186
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:09,601
My name is Yukiya Ise.

187
00:21:09,685 --> 00:21:11,853
He was from the Ise family.

188
00:21:12,396 --> 00:21:16,066
Would you like to talk to us a little more?

189
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:20,612
please hang out with me

190
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:25,492
(Erika) My purpose is only one

191
00:21:25,575 --> 00:21:27,995
I was to become a member of the Ise family.

192
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:30,956
But...

193
00:21:31,623 --> 00:21:32,958
I love those people⸺

194
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:35,836
I never thought of them as family⸺

195
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:40,340
Eventually, I will cut ties with the Ise family⸺

196
00:21:43,969 --> 00:21:46,763
I want to live with you

197
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:54,271
If you promise never to seek revenge again⸺

198
00:21:54,354 --> 00:21:55,939
May you be released⸺

199
00:21:56,023 --> 00:21:58,275
You can ask your father-in-law, though.

200
00:22:01,278 --> 00:22:04,823
If you can't do that, why don't you just stay there for the rest of your life?

201
00:22:04,906 --> 00:22:07,075
in exchange for my pride

202
00:22:16,793 --> 00:22:17,878
Erika is...

203
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:25,093
Did you really want that?

204
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:28,096
this way of life

205
00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:34,978
Degrading other people's lives and clinging to the Ise family like this.

206
00:22:39,357 --> 00:22:40,358
of course

207
00:22:44,112 --> 00:22:48,283
Me and Masayuki-san⸺

208
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:50,327
Miyabi was also achieved.

209
00:22:50,827 --> 00:22:54,373
As president, I have been given the opportunity to take on many challenges.

210
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:55,540
It's me⸺

211
00:22:57,167 --> 00:23:00,962
Every day is so fulfilling now.

212
00:23:08,011 --> 00:23:09,429
You and me⸺

213
00:23:11,056 --> 00:23:13,892
It's different from when I lived in that small house.

214
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:18,980
that's why…

215
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:25,403
Don't interfere with my happiness anymore

216
00:23:28,865 --> 00:23:30,700
I don't want you to get involved

217
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,375
So why...

218
00:23:41,128 --> 00:23:41,962
(Erika) Huh?

219
00:23:44,923 --> 00:23:47,008
So why did you come?

220
00:23:55,684 --> 00:23:59,479
(Sound of door opening and closing)

221
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:09,781
(sigh)

222
00:24:40,729 --> 00:24:43,273
- (Girl) It's delicious - (Girl) It's delicious.

223
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:47,319
- (Girl) It's delicious. - (Girl) It's delicious.

224
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:58,622
(Girl) Cute clothes

225
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:01,500
(Girl) Thank you, I bought you a new one.

226
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:04,044
-(Girl) Is that so? -(Girl) Oh, that's a rabbit.

227
00:25:04,127 --> 00:25:05,629
(Girl) Fluffy and cute

228
00:25:06,713 --> 00:25:09,591
(Sound of knocking on the door) (Male) Mr. Sato!

229
00:25:09,674 --> 00:25:11,092
Please give me back the money

230
00:25:11,176 --> 00:25:13,428
(Male) I also have a loan book today.

231
00:25:13,511 --> 00:25:15,805
Please give me back the 3 million yen!

232
00:25:15,889 --> 00:25:18,183
(Male) Open it! Hey!

233
00:25:33,990 --> 00:25:34,866
(Nobuo) Good.

234
00:25:35,742 --> 00:25:36,576
Ah...

235
00:25:41,665 --> 00:25:43,750
-(Nobuo) Too bad, always-(Seiichiro) Good, good, good.

236
00:25:43,833 --> 00:25:46,211
(Nobuo) Hehe... I also heard about Hanaho-san.

237
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:49,381
If something happens, I'll be your strength

238
00:25:49,464 --> 00:25:51,174
thank you

239
00:25:51,258 --> 00:25:54,094
...Taku Masayuki has always been like this.

240
00:25:54,177 --> 00:25:55,762
So-so So-so

241
00:25:55,845 --> 00:25:59,849
Sei-chan and I are close, so when we have a problem, we're both there. Yeah.

242
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:00,892
Helpful

243
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:03,937
(Nobuo) Hmm... What should we do over there?

244
00:26:05,689 --> 00:26:07,607
That Aoyama Police Station

245
00:26:08,775 --> 00:26:12,070
Why did you do that kind of harassment again?

246
00:26:13,905 --> 00:26:16,241
Isn't it deeply rooted in the fact that your wife was taken away?

247
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:18,285
(Seiichiro) Huh...

248
00:26:23,331 --> 00:26:24,708
(Juna) What happened?

249
00:26:25,417 --> 00:26:27,294
(Kotoko) I heard you're taking a break for a while.

250
00:26:27,377 --> 00:26:29,254
(Kina) Huh? why?

251
00:26:29,337 --> 00:26:31,047
(Kotoko) I wonder why?

252
00:26:31,631 --> 00:26:34,342
(Kina) I guess Yukini caught a cold.

253
00:26:35,176 --> 00:26:36,177
(Kotoko) Huh?

254
00:26:37,095 --> 00:26:38,680
Kina worried

255
00:26:40,598 --> 00:26:41,891
(Kotoko) That's right.

256
00:26:42,684 --> 00:26:44,477
Shall we come again tomorrow?

257
00:26:44,561 --> 00:26:46,271
-(Kina) Yeah-(Kotoko) I'm sure it'll be okay.

258
00:26:46,354 --> 00:26:48,231
-(Kina) Yeah! -(Kotoko) Yeah, hehehehe...

259
00:26:48,315 --> 00:26:49,482
Okay

260
00:26:49,566 --> 00:26:52,235
- (Girl) Ah! Kina-chan-(Girl) Ah Kina-chan

261
00:26:52,319 --> 00:26:53,778
(Girl) What were you doing just now?

262
00:27:03,705 --> 00:27:06,082
(Erika) Ah... I was back.

263
00:27:06,166 --> 00:27:07,959
Ah... yeah

264
00:27:08,543 --> 00:27:09,377
Welcome back

265
00:27:10,211 --> 00:27:11,296
I'm home

266
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:16,468
(Masayuki) Work?

267
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:18,511
Yeah, a little bit

268
00:27:18,595 --> 00:27:19,429
(Masayuki) Yeah

269
00:27:22,807 --> 00:27:25,602
Today is? Were you busy?

270
00:27:26,144 --> 00:27:27,896
Maybe not so

271
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:29,564
(Masayuki) Yeah

272
00:27:34,194 --> 00:27:36,738
Have you heard anything since then?

273
00:27:36,821 --> 00:27:38,531
No, especially

274
00:27:39,366 --> 00:27:40,825
What about your father-in-law?

275
00:27:40,909 --> 00:27:42,702
We only met this morning

276
00:27:43,286 --> 00:27:44,120
(Erika) Yeah.

277
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,543
Is it okay?

278
00:27:53,380 --> 00:27:54,464
What?

279
00:27:55,757 --> 00:27:58,134
(Masayuki) No, we

280
00:28:01,471 --> 00:28:03,098
Isn't it okay?

281
00:28:06,851 --> 00:28:09,729
If something happens, don't make that face

282
00:28:13,566 --> 00:28:14,734
(sigh)

283
00:28:14,818 --> 00:28:16,820
Are you still jumpy?

284
00:28:16,903 --> 00:28:19,364
Why don't you just get fed up?

285
00:28:20,657 --> 00:28:23,159
When I'm moving around a lot⸺

286
00:28:23,243 --> 00:28:24,536
Masayuki is always at home⸺

287
00:28:24,619 --> 00:28:28,373
It's depressing to think that you were thinking like that.

288
00:28:28,456 --> 00:28:29,958
What is it?

289
00:28:30,041 --> 00:28:34,921
Yukiya-san, who I went to see today.

290
00:28:35,004 --> 00:28:37,632
Why did you bother to talk to him?

291
00:28:37,715 --> 00:28:41,219
Stop it, I'm not inexperienced

292
00:28:43,930 --> 00:28:46,891
I told you not to get involved with me again.

293
00:28:55,775 --> 00:28:57,360
Stay strong

294
00:28:58,153 --> 00:29:00,572
You are the heir of the Ise family, right?

295
00:29:01,406 --> 00:29:04,367
Can't you do anything without your father-in-law protecting you?

296
00:29:19,841 --> 00:29:23,303
If you swear you'll never seek revenge again⸺

297
00:29:23,803 --> 00:29:24,929
May you be released⸺

298
00:29:25,013 --> 00:29:27,474
You can ask your father-in-law, though.

299
00:31:21,087 --> 00:31:22,547
Master

300
00:31:31,180 --> 00:31:34,350
I'll bring you a hot drink

301
00:31:39,981 --> 00:31:40,857
(sound of door opening)

302
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:09,135
please

303
00:32:17,352 --> 00:32:19,312
That you can do anything⸺

304
00:32:19,938 --> 00:32:23,232
I think it's okay to do anything.

305
00:32:25,526 --> 00:32:30,031
I don't want to see anyone unhappy anymore.

306
00:32:34,243 --> 00:32:35,370
surely⸺

307
00:32:37,330 --> 00:32:40,333
I think that person will be the most sad.

308
00:32:47,674 --> 00:32:51,469
I'm sorry for acting too much.

309
00:33:19,914 --> 00:33:20,832
(Masayuki) Erika

310
00:33:46,315 --> 00:33:47,150
Huh?

311
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:52,947
What are you doing! ?

312
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:54,031
what?

313
00:33:54,532 --> 00:33:57,160
What... Huh?

314
00:33:57,243 --> 00:33:58,995
Why stop?

315
00:33:59,662 --> 00:34:00,913
Something like this⸺

316
00:34:01,456 --> 00:34:05,334
Miyabi would feel bad if she found him when she grew up, right?

317
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:08,880
(Masayuki) Huh?

318
00:34:08,963 --> 00:34:09,964
what?

319
00:34:10,965 --> 00:34:12,258
Any problem?

320
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:16,262
No, it's not a problem...

321
00:34:21,851 --> 00:34:23,352
(Erika) Pull this out!

322
00:34:23,436 --> 00:34:24,812
What do you want?

323
00:34:26,522 --> 00:34:27,857
feel ill

324
00:34:32,445 --> 00:34:33,279
Huh?

325
00:34:44,916 --> 00:34:46,626
(Erika) “Everyone from the Ise family”

326
00:34:46,709 --> 00:34:50,379
“I write this letter hoping that it will arrive safely.”

327
00:34:50,463 --> 00:34:53,341
“This time it was my thoughtless idea⸺”

328
00:34:53,424 --> 00:34:56,135
“I harassed everyone in the Ise family⸺”

329
00:34:56,219 --> 00:34:58,471
“I am really sorry”

330
00:34:58,554 --> 00:35:00,890
“I deeply regret it.”

331
00:35:01,474 --> 00:35:04,435
“I promise I will never seek revenge again⸺”

332
00:35:04,519 --> 00:35:06,938
“Please get me out of here”

333
00:35:07,563 --> 00:35:08,439
“Please me”…

334
00:35:08,523 --> 00:35:09,816
Enough is enough

335
00:35:10,399 --> 00:35:12,276
This is definitely a lie

336
00:35:13,027 --> 00:35:14,695
get carried away

337
00:35:19,575 --> 00:35:23,121
I also agree with Masayuki-san.

338
00:35:23,996 --> 00:35:25,123
Excuse me

339
00:35:30,419 --> 00:35:35,049
footsteps)

340
00:35:35,132 --> 00:35:36,425
(policeman) number 31

341
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:42,640
Released.

342
00:35:44,642 --> 00:35:46,644
‪♪～

343
00:36:37,570 --> 00:36:38,988
Well then

344
00:36:46,746 --> 00:36:48,748
‪～♪

345
00:37:14,398 --> 00:37:17,109
(Erika) There's no way you can destroy the Ise family.

346
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:19,111
my Ise family

347
00:37:19,195 --> 00:37:22,531
(Seiichiro) Could you cut ties with the Ise family now?

348
00:37:22,615 --> 00:37:25,493
Why are you so obsessed with us?

349
00:37:25,576 --> 00:37:28,871
(Masayuki as a child) The very fact that you were born into this world was an accident.

350
00:37:41,050 --> 00:37:42,969
- (Male) It's dangerous, it's dangerous - (Yukiya as a child) Mother!

351
00:37:43,052 --> 00:37:44,929
-(Male) No-(Yukiya) Mom!

352
00:37:45,012 --> 00:37:46,389
(Yukiya) What about your mother?

353
00:37:47,223 --> 00:37:48,891
give me back my mom

354
00:37:48,975 --> 00:37:50,101
Get out.

355
00:37:50,184 --> 00:37:52,812
Yukiya can't do anything anyway.

356
00:37:52,895 --> 00:37:54,605
Look aside

357
00:37:58,401 --> 00:37:59,360
I...

358
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:10,496
I will never forgive you

359
00:38:12,957 --> 00:38:14,667
 (Yukiya) I'm different from you⸺

360
00:38:14,750 --> 00:38:16,210
I have nothing to lose

361
00:38:16,293 --> 00:38:18,587
(Seiichiro) I thought I had to talk to you someday.

362
00:38:18,671 --> 00:38:19,630
Don't be silly!

363
00:38:19,714 --> 00:38:22,758
(Erika) Maybe it's best to take it easy.

364
00:38:22,842 --> 00:38:24,468
About your father-in-law

365
00:38:24,552 --> 00:38:27,555
You will continue to be punished until you die.
